### Terrain Tactician
*2nd level Skirmisher feature*

Your skill on the battlefield is unmatched, regardless of which battlefield you find yourself on. You gain passive combat benefits based on the terrain you're standing in, as detailed below. If a locale is very similar but not explicitly described as something from the table, you gain those respective bonuses.

You gain additional Provincial Prowess bonuses at 6th and 11th level.

{{classTable,frame
##### Provincial Prowess Bonuses by Terrain:
| Terrain Type | Bonus |
|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| City / Kingdom / Town | You gain a climbing speed equal to your movement speed to climb buildings. When you take the Hide action while using rooftops as cover, you have a +5 to your Stealth roll.
|  Fields/ Grasslands/ Plains  | Your movement speed increases by 10 ft. 
| Forest / Grove/ Woods | You gain a Climbing speed equal to your movement speed to climb trees and nonmagical Difficult, Loose, and Hazardous terrain doesn't affect you.
|  Crags/ Hills/ Mountains  | You gain a Climbing speed equal to your movement speed to climb trees and nonmagical Difficult, Loose, and Hazardous terrain doesn't affect you. 
|  Arid/ Desert/ Dunes  | Loose terrain doesn't affect you and any rolls you make in order to resist being knocked prone are made at advantage.
|  Coast/ Ocean / Sea  | You have a swimming speed equal to your walking speed. 
|  Arctic/ Glacial/ Icy  | Your movement speed cannot be reduced as a result of the weather or nonmagical effects. 
| Bog/ Poisonous/ Swamp| Any rolls you make to resist effects that poison you are made at advantage, and you have resistance to Poison damage.
| Dark / Dungeon / Void | You gain Blindsight out to a range of 30 ft. If you already have Blindsight out to any range, this range increases to 60 ft. unless your Blindsight already exceeds this amount.
| Fire / Lava / Volcanic | Any extreme weather effects that would normally damage do not. You have resistance to Fire damage.
| Other | Talk with your DM to determine a minor feature that fits the terrain.
}}

### Spellcasting
*2nd level Skirmisher feature*

By the time you reach 2nd level, you have learned to use the magical essence of nature to cast spells, much as a druid does. See Spells Rules for the general rules of spellcasting and the Spells Listing for the Skirmisher spell list.
