###### Spells Known of 1st Level and Higher
You know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the Skirmisher spell list.

The Spells Known column of the Skirmisher table shows when you learn more Skirmisher spells of your choice. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For instance, when you reach 5th level in this class, you can learn one new spell of 1st or 2nd level.

Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the Skirmisher spells you know and replace it with another spell from the Skirmisher spell list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots.

<div style='margin-top:20px'></div>

{{note
###### Spellcasting Ability
Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your Skirmisher spells, since your magic draws on your attunement to nature. You use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a Skirmisher spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.

Spell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

Spell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier

When casting spells, subtract 5 from the start-up and cool-down initiative impacts of cast spells. You cannot reduce either initiative impacts to a number below 0.
}}


\page

### Expertise
*3rd level Skirmisher feature*

At 3rd level, choose two of your Skill Proficiencies. Your Proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses that Chosen skill.

You can also speak, read, and write two additional languages of your choice.

### Skirmisher Archetype
*3rd level Skirmisher feature*

At 3rd level, you choose an archetype that you strive to emulate: the Hunter that is detailed at the end of the class description or one from another source. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at **7th**, **11th**, and **15th** level.

##### Options:
<u>TBD</u>

### Quick Switch

Starting at 3rd Level, your squat reflexes while in the midst of combat become swift enough to let you swap weaponry at a moment's notice. You can draw and stow any number of weapons at any time during your turn without any Initiative Impact. 

If you reduce a creature to 0 hit points with a melee weapon attack and hit a creature with a ranged weapon attack in the same turn, apply your damage modifier to the ranged weapon attack twice. 

If you reduce a creature to 0 hit points with a ranged weapon attack and hit a creature with a melee weapon attack in the same turn, apply your damage modifier to the melee weapon attack twice.


### Ability Score Improvement
When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th levels, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.

If your DM allows the use of feats, you may instead take a feat.

### Extra Attack
*5th level Skirmisher feature*

**At 5th level**, When you take the attack action, you may attack twice instead of once. additionally your initiative impact for taking the attack action is reduced from 20 to 18.

**At 15th level**, you can make 3 attacks on your turn at the cost of only 16 initiative impact when you take the attack action


\column

### Eye for Trouble Improvement
*6th level Skirmisher feature*

When you use the Observe action against a creature with a Challenge Rating higher than your Skirmisher Level, treat your Skirmisher level as 2 levels higher. You automatically succeed on the Wisdom (Insight) check if your level exceeds the Challenge Rating of the target.

### Terrain Tactician Improvement
*6th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 6th level, on top of any bonuses gained at 2nd level, additional combat benefits are gained based on the terrain you're standing in, as detailed below.

{{classTable,frame
##### Provincial Prowess Bonuses by Terrain:
| Terrain Type | Bonus |
|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| City / Kingdom / Town | You can choose to subtract 5 from your Initiative Impact at the end of your turns.
|  Fields/ Grasslands/ Plains  | When you take the Hide action while using tall grass as cover, you have a +5 to your Stealth roll. 
| Forest / Grove/ Woods | When you take the Hide action while using trees as cover, you have a +5 to Stealth roll. 
|  Crags/ Hills/ Mountains  | Attack rolls made against creatures standing on nonmagical Difficult, Loose, and Hazardous terrain are made at advantage. 
|  Arid/ Desert/ Dunes  | If a creature within 5 ft. of you attempts to knock you prone and is within 10 initiative of your next turn, you can use an Interrupt action to instead impose the effect on the creature. 
|  Coast/ Ocean / Sea  | Your vision is not limited while attacking underwater and none of your weapon attacks suffer negative effects as a result of attacking underwater. 
|  Arctic/ Glacial/ Icy  | When you take the Hide action when using snow or ice as cover, you have a +5 to your Stealth roll. 
| Bog/ Poisonous/ Swamp| You have advantage on any rolls made to resist falling prone. You have Blindsight on any creatures within 30 ft. of you that are standing in water.
| Dark / Dungeon / Void | Nonmagical OR Magical Hazardous terrain doesn't affect you.
| Fire / Lava / Volcanic | Hazardous Terrain that isn't lava or a lava equivalent doesn't affect you.
| Other | Talk with your DM to determine an intermediate feature that fits the terrain.
}}

\page
<div style='margin-top:40px'></div>

### Steady Breath
*8th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 8th level, if you are within 20 initiative of your next turn, you can use an Interrupt action to give yourself a number of temporary hit points equal to 1d8 + your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1 temporary hit point) for an initiative impact of 5. You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.

In addition, whenever you finish a short rest, your exhaustion level, if any, is decreased by 1.

<div style='margin-top:120px'></div>

