### Terrain Tactician Improvement
*11th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 11th level, on top of any bonuses gained at 2nd and 6th level, additional combat benefits are gained based on the terrain you're standing in, as detailed below.

{{classTable,frame
##### Provincial Prowess Bonuses by Terrain:
| Terrain Type | Bonus |
|:-----:|:-----------------:|
| City / Kingdom / Town | You automatically succeed on any Wisdom (Perception) rolls made to reveal unseen creatures, and your Passive Perception has a +10 for any creature attempting to Hide from your sight.
|  Fields/ Grasslands/ Plains  | Once per turn, when you make an attack roll against a creature while hidden in tall grass, you can move up to 10 feet (if you have enough movement to do so) and choose to take the Hide action as a part of the Attack action without an addition to your Initiative Impact. 
| Forest / Grove/ Woods | Once per turn, you can teleport to a tree within 30 ft. of you (initiative impact of 10). Doing so doesn't reveal your location to creatures that are unaware of your presence.
|  Crags/ Hills/ Mountains  | You can walk up, down, and across vertical and upside down surfaces.
|  Arid/ Desert/ Dunes  | Prone creatures on Loose terrain are always attacked at advantage as a result of the condition.
|  Coast/ Ocean / Sea  | Any attack that hits a creature that cannot see you within Dim Light or Darkness as a result of lacking underwater visibility is a critical hit.
|  Arctic/ Glacial/ Icy  | Any attack that hits a creature that is standing in Difficult terrain or has had their movement speed reduced is a critical hit.
| Bog/ Poisonous/ Swamp| Your weapon attacks deal an additional 1d6 Poison damage. This damage does normal damage to creatures with Resistance to Poison damage and half damage to creatures that are immune to Poison damage.
| Dark / Dungeon / Void | Attack rolls made against terrain automatically hit. If a creature you hit with a weapon attack is within 10 ft. of Hazardous terrain, you can subject them to a Strength Saving Throw equal to your Spell Save DC. On a failed save, the creature is pulled into Hazardous Terrain within range and suffers its effects as if it willingly entered it.
| Fire / Lava / Volcanic | If a creature you hit with a weapon attack is within 10 ft. of Hazardous terrain, you can subject them to a Strength Saving Throw equal to your Spell Save DC. On a failed save, the creature is pulled into Hazardous Terrain within range and suffers its effects as if it willingly entered it.
| Other | Talk with your DM to determine an advanced feature that fits the terrain.
}}

<img 
  src='https://i.imgur.com/pFGtKAj.png'
  style='position:absolute;top:475px;right:300px;width:700px;mix-blend-mode:multiply'/>
	<div style='margin-top:800px'></div>

\page
	
### Spell Combat
*11th level Skirmisher feature*

At 11th level when you take the attack action, you can replace one of your attack rolls with a spell that has an instant casting time and an initiative impact of no more than 10. You do not suffer additional initiative impact from casting this spell.

### Peerless Beholding
*14th level Skirmisher feature*

Beginning at 14th level, you are no longer limited by your Wisdom modifier when using the Observe action. You also learn every Saving Throw modifier the creature has on a successful observation.

Additionally, (something else goes here but it's getting late).

### Jack of All Blades
*18th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 18th level, if you hit with three seperate weapons in a single turn, the third hit is a critical hit.

### Split-Second Reactions
*20th level Skirmisher feature*

Starting at 20th level, whenever you take an Interrupt action, you can do so without the initiative count having to be within 10 of your next turn. Additionally, all Interrupt Actions don't increase your initiative impact.

